,Recommended,600720,31938753,Posted: 24 May,all,lol?,"Been playing the game a week before release during the closed beta. From what I've experienced, it's exactly the same as all the other TM games; easy to pick up, hard to master, and very, very, very addictive.Environment looks beautiful. It's a unique looking and feeling environment and really adds well to the series.As for the track editor blocks, there's a good selection and they look great. My only gripe is that there needs to be more transitional blocks; i.e, platforms with small lips and shallow changes in height or camber.The car physics are great. For you TM fans out there, imagine a mix of Island and Bay from United, but with drift physics of Canyon. That is literally what this car feels like... and I love it.Graphics are beautiful, so you video editors (and myself) will have a ball doing scenery or action videos due to the great environment, and the car physics make stunts very easy :)If you have never played a TM game before and are interested in picking this up, go for it. It's tons of fun and I can fully recommend. If you are a die hard Trackmania fan, then why are you reading this? Go buy it now!"
