76561198032360788,Recommended,600720,33177586,Posted: 3 July,all,Catalyst,"I am not a new player of Trackmania, a long time ago I had played United Forever and I was absolutely found of this game.Recently, I just heard that there was a new Trackmania which was going to be released, I hadn't heared about Turbo and I was so happy to be able to replay a serie that I thought was dead.So yeah I really enjoyed this game and I'm gonna make a review of what my experience was like :So, first, I'm tired of these peoples complaining ""The interface sucks, it's ugly as hell"" . This argument is just false because this is just a question about personal tastes. They are also complaining about the fact that it is difficult to understand, where I do not agree simply because I hadn't any problems understanding it.Second, the difficulty, yeah, I agree the game is really easy until red tracks, but I do not think it is that bad, It makes the game way better for new players because it gives them the time to adapt to the controls until the finally get to the hard tracks. So the difficulty curve should need a higher difficulty overall, I totally agree on that point but it makes the game good for newcomers, which is why I think it is good enough.Third, the editor, I absolutely need to find a way to play united again because I hear that Lagoon's editor is not as good as the one from United, but from what I remember, the editor was really good in united but I can't see in any ways why it is better than the one in Lagoon. The one in Lagoon even has mixmapping and airmapping which are both awesome features that weren't in United Forever.Fourth, the game lacks community. YEAAH, cannot say anything against that, it is rare to find a server with at least one person in. So yeah :| Lagoon definitely lacks a communityFifth, Lack of split screen, no, the game doesn't lack split screen, it just lacks the campaign maps, you can still play on your own maps. Because of the kind of recent Maniaplanet 4 update, the campaign tracks are lacking in splitscreen, so, yeah, huge bad fact about the game, but It's not like you can't play split screen, you can still play in your own maps, wich I loved to show to my friends.So yeah I hoped this review helped you and I really do hope you will enjoy the game"
