76561198025331540,Recommended,600720,33152876,Posted: 2 July,all,SneakyTT,"Been hearing about this Trackmania series for years, and finally decided to check it out.The game, at its heart, is a series of time trials on short courses, with very appealing visuals, sounds, and physics. I love how it strips away all the usual racing game elements - like story, dialogue, car choices, tuning, etc. It's just a pure racing experience, which is a joy to play.However, Trackmania 2 Lagoon is one part of a larger game ""system"" called Maniaplanet, which is very confusing at first - though once you wrap your mind around it, it all kind of makes sense.Besides Lagoon, there are a number of other racing environments, such as Stadium, Canyon, and Valley - each of which you need to buy separately - bu they're all kind of mixed together on Maniaplanet. There's also a first-person shooting game system mixed in as well.I started off with the demo, which I eventually discovered was a free version of all the games, where you can only play one ""channel"" at a time. But, this means you can play Trackmania for free as long as you want, but just one channel at a time. So you may need to wait awhile before Lagoon comes up.You can design your own courses. And there are public server where you can race online with others on a series of player-designed courses. The more I play, the more I am discovering about this whole system.But anyway, just the solo time trial mode in Lagoon is well worth the price.Don't let all the complications of the interface keep you away... the game itself is pure addictive video game pleasure."
