76561197970585058,Recommended,600720,31998195,Posted: 27 May,all,Varkster,"Addmittedly I've only just started with this, and bought it more to support general TM development rather than because I felt it'd be my kind of thing. With >8k hours on TM2 stadium, this one didn't really appeal to me as much, even on paper.But first impressions are even worse than I expected.Astonishingly twitchy controls, tracks that seem to go for 'wow' factor above drivability, absolutely terrible choice of camera angles, no ability to select my monitor's resolution in-game (I had to use the launcher) and a (solo) ranking system that broke after only 3 tracks.I'm still going to recommend it, because if you liked Turbo more than the TM2 games, this is quite probably for you. It lacks some of the 'console gen' irksomeness of Turbo, while at the same time including envionment/controls and track blocks much more like that title.Probably back to TM2 Stadium for me, though."
